(22059, 283, '2012-07-02 11:01:47', '2012-07-02 17:01:47', 'Joe Cannon is the former chair of the Utah Republican Party and is currently editor of the Deseret Morning News in Salt Lake City.\r\n\r\nJoe was named editor of the <em>Deseret Morning News </em>on December 8, 2006. Cannon was a candidate for the U.S. Senate in 1992 (defeated by current Senator Robert F. Bennett) and served as an assistant administrator of the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency from 1983 - 1985. He was Chairman of the Utah Republican Party from 2002 to 2006. Cannon served a mission for the LDS Church, and also for a time served on the Isle of Man. Cannon received a degree in political science and, in 1977, a law degree from Brigham Young University.', 'Joe Cannon', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'joe-cannon', '', '', '2012-10-01 17:03:07', '2012-10-01 23:03:07', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22059', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22066, 283, '2012-07-02 11:02:07', '2012-07-02 17:02:07', 'Brandon Mull resides in a happy little valley near the mouth of a canyon with his wife and three children. He spent two years living in the Atacama Desert of Northern Chile where he learned Spanish and juggling. He once won a pudding eating contest in the park behind his grandma’s house, earning a gold medal. Brandon is the author of the New York Times bestselling Fablehaven series and The Candy Shop War.', 'Brandon Mull', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'brandon-mull', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:59:50', '2012-10-01 22:59:50', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22066', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22068, 283, '2012-07-02 11:02:24', '2012-07-02 17:02:24', 'Larry Gelwix has been the coach of the Highland Rugby team since its founding in Salt Lake City in 1973. The movie <em>Forever Strong  </em>(2008) was inspired by him and his team''s history. The Highland rugby team has compiled an unrivaled winning record since its founding in 1973. Gelwix is a native of California. He served a mission for The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in the midwestern Central States Mission. He has bachelors and masters degrees from Brigham Young University in Organizational Communication. He also played rugby for three years at BYU under coaches from New Zealand. He became an instructor at Church seminary adjacent to Highland High to earn money to pursue a doctorate at Purdue University. He became an assistant football coach during the fall season and a wrestling coach in the winter. He missed coaching in the spring, and having played rugby at BYU, decided to start a rugby team at the high school.   Gelwix quit teaching seminary full time after four years and opened a travel agency in 1979.  He coaches rugby in the evenings. Rugby is not an official high school sport and the team must raise all funds required, including travel. All 11 coaches are volunteers. When the movie <em>Forever Strong</em> was made, Gelwix was not paid for his story. Gelwix insisted that the movie had to be about the players and not him. Gelwix and his wife Cathy are the parents of five children. Known as the <em>Getaway Guru</em>, Gelwix has for 17 years been the co-host of The Travel Show, a weekend program heard on KNRS Radio in Salt Lake City and various stations throughout the Intermountain West region.', 'Larry Gelwix', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'larry-gelwix', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:57:29', '2012-10-01 22:57:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22068', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22070, 283, '2012-07-02 11:02:39', '2012-07-02 17:02:39', 'The four time Billboard charting recording artist Paul Cardall has inspired people worldwide. Not only as a songwriter, composer, and performer, but He has been successful running his own independent record label Stone Angel Music for more than 10 years.   As a kid he tried piano lessons as an 8 year old but quit after less than a year. As a teenager, Cardall discovered his gift of music after a friend’s tragic death. He found solace through the family piano.  Over the next several years, Cardall spent hours at the piano perfecting his gift. He spent time with popular piano instructor Craig Kaelin who helped critique Cardall''s music, taught improvisation skills, and shed new light on chord structures.  Cardall was also busy learning he had a gift of working with people.\n\nAfter serving a 2-year mission for his Church he was recruited by Salt Lake Community College with a full ride leadership scholarship.  He was involved in student affairs, serving as the Fine Arts President and Public Relations Vice-President. He had the opportunity to work as a board member with a 6-figure budget, coordinating hundreds of events for students and people in the community. He oversaw events with local and national performers, poets, and authors. He also served as President of the Student Leadership Council and was able to help the college administration with organizing recruiting activities.   During his college experience, Cardall took jobs playing the piano for tips in Nordstrom and in fine dining restaurants in Salt Lake City, Utah. Many customers requested a CD of his music, and so in 1994 he Paul recorded his first album titled <em>Sign of Affection</em>.  A copy made its way to #1 New York Times best-selling author Richard Paul Evans, writer of <em>The Christmas Box</em>. In 1995 he invited Cardall to create a musical adaptation of his story. Consequently, Cardall was able to work with Evans coordinating tours and other events surrounding the release of the CD and the book. The resulting album sold tens of thousands of copies its first year.   Cardall continued to serve his community as a counselor for Brigham Young University’s Family Program Especially for Youth Camp.  His responsibilities included planning and executing events for hundreds of teenagers. During this time, as fans of Cardall’s music continued to grow, he became serious about a career.\n\nIn 1999, Cardall became a full-time artist when he signed a multi-album deal with Narada, a division of Virgin Records America. After releasing 2 albums with Narada, including a re-release of <em>The Christmas Box </em>Cardall left to start his own record label, Stone Angel Music.  Stone Angel Music distributes his music all over the world. This distribution includes license deals with Orange Music in Singapore, Bon Music in South Korea, and San Pablo Music in Spain. Overall, Cardall has released thirteen studio albums, many of which have debuted on Billboard Charts.   In addition to his own music career, Cardall’s label has signed cellist Steven Sharp Nelson, whose <em>Sacred Cello</em> debuted on the Billboard Classical Charts; guitarist'' Jake White, and film composer Ryan Stewart, who scores orchestral works for the SCI-FI Channel, and guitarist Ryan Tilby from the Capitol Music group Ryan Shup &amp; The Rubberband.', 'Paul Cardall', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'paul-cardall', '', '', '2012-10-03 12:25:36', '2012-10-03 18:25:36', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22070', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22071, 283, '2012-07-02 11:04:24', '2012-07-02 17:04:24', 'Rodney Hawes is on the National Advisory Council of the Marriott School of Business at BYU and is a member of the Board of Dean’s Advisors at Harvard Business School. He is the former Chairman and CEO of Life Re Corporation and founded the Investment Associates of New Canaan, Connecticut. His entrepreneurial endeavors include computer software companies, consumer products, and developing the Five Guys Burgers and Fries franchise in several western states. Brother Hawes is a military graduate from Stanford and has an MBA from Harvard.', 'Rod Hawes', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rod-hawes', '', '', '2012-10-03 09:01:53', '2012-10-03 15:01:53', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22071', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22072, 283, '2012-07-02 11:03:00', '2012-07-02 17:03:00', 'Quarterback coach for BYU football team. He<strong> </strong>has coached 4 bowl games. A unanimous All-Mountain West Conference selection and Heisman Trophy candidate in 2001, "The Domanator" led the Cougars to a 12-2 season as a senior with 3,542 yards passing, in 2001 he was 261-of-408 with 33 touchdown passes and rushed for 503 yards and eight touchdowns. Led BYU to a 14-2 record as a starter, ... brothers Kevin, Bryce and Cliff also played for BYU. Doman played three seasons as a quarterback in the NFL. Selected by the San Francisco 49ers in the fifth round of the 2002 NFL Draft, where he spent the majority of the three seasons. In 2002, Doman also played for the Buffalo Bills and Washington Redskins before returning to San Francisco in 2004. Doman graduated from BYU [2002, B.S in business]; Skyline H.S.[Salt Lake City, 1995]. He served a mission to Bahia Blanca, Argentina.  Doman and his wife Alisha have three children: a daughter and two sons.', 'Brandon Doman', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'brandon-doman', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:47:45', '2012-10-01 22:47:45', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22072', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22074, 283, '2012-07-02 11:03:21', '2012-07-02 17:03:21', 'Shane Pope is a systems engineer for Cisco Systems. Over the past eight  years Shane has donated of  his time to share his technical knowledge with families concerned with protecting their children from the dangers of the Internet. Shane talks with you and adult groups about such issues as the dangers of Internet pornography, Internet predators, and improper cell phone usage such as sexting, spamming, phishing, cyber bullying, and proper Social Networking techniques.', 'Shane Pope', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'shane-pope', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:45:34', '2012-10-01 22:45:34', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22074', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22076, 283, '2012-07-02 11:03:38', '2012-07-02 17:03:38', 'Henry J. Erying is an administrator at BYU-Idaho.', 'Henry J. Eyring', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'henry-j-eyring', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:44:29', '2012-10-01 22:44:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22076', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22118, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:36:16', '2012-07-17 21:36:16', '<p><strong>John W. Rockwell</strong> has spent his life teaching students history, especially U.S. history and history of the Wild West. He taught in Duchesne, Utah, and then in Taylorsville, Utah, at Eisenhower Junior High and Taylorsville High School for most of his career. He received the Distinguished Faculty Award from the National Honors Society in 2008. John has also worked on the Lehi City Historical Preservation Commission and has been involved in historical restoration and preservation projects throughout Lehi, Utah. John served an LDS mission in Mexico and has followed his ancestor Porter’s footsteps with a lifelong service in the Church.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Jerry Borrowman</strong> has written numerous articles in both Church and financial publications, including the <em>Church News </em>and the <em>Ensign</em> magazine. He is the author of the best-selling series ’Til the Boys Come Home as well as the novelette <em>One Christmas Eve.</em> He has also coauthored several biographies, including the award-winning <em>Three Against Hitler</em> with Rudi Wobbe, <em>A Distant Prayer</em> with Joseph Banks, and <em>Beyond the Call of Duty</em> with Bernie Fisher. Jerry Borrowman and Rudi Wobbe won the National Award of the Freedoms Foundation at Valley Forge for their contribution to promoting the cause of freedom through their writing. His latest book, <em>Stories from the Life of Porter Rockwell, </em>was co-authored by John W. Rockwell, great-great grandson of Porter Rockwell. Jerry and his wife, Marcella, live in Sandy, Utah.</p>', 'John Rockwell &amp; Jerry Borrowman', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'john-rockwell-jerry-borrowman', '', '', '2012-10-02 14:31:02', '2012-10-02 20:31:02', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22118', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22120, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:36:41', '2012-07-17 21:36:41', 'Matthew Holland has held several leadership positions in higher education. He was the associate director of BYU''s London Study Abroad Program in 2008.  Holland has taught a variety of courses including American Heritage, Modern Political Philosophy, and Public Ethics. Since 1996, Holland has worked as a part‑ time independent management consultant. He also worked as a special assistant to Governor Michael O. Leavitt from 1992 to 1994 and as Chief of Staff to the CEO of the Monitor Group in Cambridge, Massachusetts from 1992 to 1994.\r\n\r\nHolland holds doctorate and master degrees in political science from Duke University and a bachelor''s degree in political science from BYU. From 2005‑ 2006, he served as a Fellow in the James Madison Program in American Ideals and Institutions at Princeton University, and as the Raoul Wallenberg Scholar at Hebrew University of Jerusalem in 1991. Holland is the son of Elder Jeffrey R. Holland of Quorum of the Twelve of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints. The elder Holland also is a former president of BYU.', 'Matthew Holland', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'matthew-holland', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:28:10', '2012-10-01 22:28:10', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22120', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22123, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:37:13', '2012-07-17 21:37:13', 'Since becoming head coach of the BYU men''s basketball program in 2005, Dave Rose has guided the Cougars to an impressive array of on-the-court awards and accolades while his unassuming approach to service and the community has been recognized at the top of his profession. He was a member of national sensation "Phi Slama Jama" the University of Houston''s college basketball squad that finished as national runner-up in the 1983 NCAA Men''s Division I Basketball Tournament. Rose first came to BYU as an assistant in 1997 to help newly hired head coach Steve Cleveland rebuild the Cougar program. A native of Houston, Texas, Rose and his wife Cheryl have three children and two grandchildren.', 'Dave Rose', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dave-rose', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:26:00', '2012-10-01 22:26:00', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22123', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22126, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:37:28', '2012-07-17 21:37:28', 'Heather is a member of the League of Utah Writers and LDStorymakers. She is the author of “Women of the Book of Mormon” and the “Out of Jerusalem” series.\r\n\r\nHeather was born in Providence, Rhode Island, but spent most of her childhood in Orem, Utah. During these years, her family traveled back and forth between the Middle East and Utah. At the age of eight, while living in Egypt, she was baptized in the Red Sea. Heather attended the Anglican School of Jerusalem from 1987-88, and returned again to Jerusalem with her husband in 1994.\r\n\r\nAlthough Heather graduated from Brigham Young University with a major in Fashion Merchandising and minor in Business Management, she always dreamed of writing novels. That opportunity came in 2001 when her husband moved his home office to an outside location. The empty office with a blank computer screen was too tempting for Heather to resist.\r\n\r\nHeather is a member of the League of Utah Writers and LDStorymakers. She has served as a Chapter President and Chapter Secretary of the League of Utah Writers. Heather has received several awards from the League for her national fiction work. Committed to honing her writing skills, she meets each week with a writer''s critique group. Heather lives in Lehi, with her husband Chris, and their four children, Kaelin, Kara, Dana, and Rose. She also enjoys reading, sewing, and spending time with her family.', 'Heather Moore', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'heather-moore', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:22:44', '2012-10-01 22:22:44', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22126', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22129, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:37:39', '2012-07-17 21:37:39', 'Guy is an Associate Academic Vice President at BYU-Idaho. As a Colonel with the Army National Guard, Guy served a tour in Iraq developing and overseeing the training for the Iraqi Army.', 'Guy Hollingsworth', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'guy-hollingsworth', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:17:50', '2012-10-01 22:17:50', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22129', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22131, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:37:58', '2012-07-17 21:37:58', 'Paul is an entrepreneur who is involved in many companies and ventures. He is the cofounder of OGIO International and VideoSeminarLive.com.', 'Paul Taggart', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'paul-taggart', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:14:39', '2012-10-01 22:14:39', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22131', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22134, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:38:13', '2012-07-17 21:38:13', 'Tracy is the Founder, owner and CEO of <a title="http://ABCbabyfurniture.com/" href="http://ABCbabyfurniture.com/" target="_blank">ABCbabyfurniture.com</a> as well as a stay-at-home mom of four.', 'Tracy Joost', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tracy-joost', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:13:30', '2012-10-01 22:13:30', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22134', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22140, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:38:35', '2012-07-17 21:38:35', 'Heidi Swinton is an award-winning author and screenwriter whose works include To the Rescue: The Biography of Thomas S. Monson. PBS documentaries <em>American Prophet; Sacred Stone; Sweetwater Rescue; Trail of Hope;</em> and <em>America’s Choir.</em> She has served on the Relief Society general board and as a member of Church writing committees. She served with her husband, Jeffrey C. Swinton, as he presided over the England London South Mission (2006-2009); they are the parents of five sons, four living, and have four daughters-in-law and six grandchildren.', 'Heidi Swinton', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'heidi-swinton', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:45:25', '2012-10-01 21:45:25', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22140', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22142, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:38:49', '2012-07-17 21:38:49', 'Bro. Lund served as a member of the Second Quorum of the Seventy in The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints form 2002 to 2008. He holds B.A. and M.S. degrees from Brigham Young University and also did additional graduate work at Pepperdine University and the University of Judaism in California. He worked for the Church Educational System for 35 years as a teacher, curriculum writer, and zone administrator. A prolific author of both doctrinal works and fiction, he is best known for his historical novels: The work and the Glory series, Fire of the Covenant, and The Kingdom and the Crown series.\r\n\r\nHe and his wife, Lynn, are the parents of seven children and live in Alpine, Utah.', 'Gerald Lund', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'gerald-lund', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:43:48', '2012-10-01 21:43:48', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22142', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22145, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:39:04', '2012-07-17 21:39:04', 'Part-time BYU-Idaho Employee. Russian Immigrant with great story of how he came to U.S. and joined the Church.', 'Wally Siwachok', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'wally-siwachok', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:41:17', '2012-10-01 21:41:17', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22145', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22150, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:39:16', '2012-07-17 21:39:16', 'Jason Buck was born in Moses Lake, Washington, to a family of eight children with a rich farming tradition. When he was three years old his father moved the family to Michigan to farm potatoes. Jason’s storybook childhood came crashing down around him at six years old when his family lost their farm. He will never forget the tears in his father’s eyes as they stood on the front yard watching the farm equipment being taken away. He swore at that moment that he would make things right and nothing in the world would stop him. He knew, even at that age, that the NFL was his answer, and even though athletics was not a part of his family, Jason pursued it with every fiber of his soul. The harder life became for him and his family, the more determined he was to correct it.\r\n\r\nEvery day of his life from that point forward was a great challenge: overcoming adversity in almost every imaginable form. As you hear about his challenges you will fight with Jason for his very survival as his family suffers devastating financial hardships, becomes homeless, sleeping in the dirt under a hay truck, bathes in the cattle’s watering trough and finding clothes in the county dump. Fight with him for his dreams, his self-worth, and his identity as he defends himself and his family to all those that looked down upon, ridiculed, and persecuted them. See, through Jason’s eyes, his family falling apart under the pressure: parents fighting and talking of divorce and siblings dropping out of high school or running away from home. As his world crumbles around him, fight with him through persecution by teachers, coaches, and teammates, hazing, injuries, a tragic death, eventual divorce, and challenges no one should have to face.\r\n\r\nYou will fight side by side with Jason as he continues to work through insurmountable odds and adversity, coming from a redneck high school with a graduating class of 25 students and walking on as a quarterback at a local junior college only to leave the team because he couldn’t pay tuition; working at a seed mill for $3.25 an hour while lifting weights every night in order to come back two years later to become an All-American defensive lineman; winning the Outland Trophy and being drafted as the 17th player in the 1st round of the NFL draft to play in two Super Bowls! His story has the power to change lives.\r\n\r\nSince retiring from the NFL Jason has stayed active in the football world by being a trusted sports analyst and color commentator for the regional ABC, CBS, NBC and FOX networks; a coach for his two son’s teams; and as an owner of the Utah Blaze of the Arena Football League. He is also an active motivational speaker sharing his inspirational story and the principles of success that he has lived by to universities, corporations and other assorted groups throughout the United States. Motivational speaking has always been a great love of Jason’s, and now that his family is older, he is expanding his speaking schedule, writing his autobiography, and completing a documentary film of his life with Phil Tuckett, formerly of NFL Films. (You will have to ask Jason how they came together; that in itself is a great story.)\r\n\r\nThroughout this time, Jason’s number-one life focus has been his wife, Roxi, of 28 years and his children and grandchildren. Now that his family is older, Jason is ready to complete these great projects documenting his life story, which he absolutely loves sharing. He truly appreciates the effects it can have on so many people, and he looks forward to inspiring many others over many more years!', 'Jason Buck', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jason-buck', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:40:27', '2012-10-01 21:40:27', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22150', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22152, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:40:19', '2012-07-17 21:40:19', 'Student Services &amp; Activities Vice President at BYU-Idaho.', 'Kevin Miyasaki', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kevin-miyasaki', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:39:26', '2012-10-01 21:39:26', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22152', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22154, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:41:03', '2012-07-17 21:41:03', 'Brent has conducted in-depth research on transformational figures—people who effect positive change in others’ lives--and shares insights from his studies and personal life. Brent earned a Ph.D. form the University of Idaho in Adult Education. He is a faculty member in the Communication Department at Brigham Young University-Idaho.', 'Brent Bean', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'brent-bean', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:36:05', '2012-10-01 21:36:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22154', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22156, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:41:16', '2012-07-17 21:41:16', 'David is president of Enough to Spare, a non-profit organization that helps provide educational opportunities for children in Uganda. David is a faculty member in the Department of History, Geography and Political Science at Brigham Young University-Idaho.', 'David Pigott', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'david-pigott', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:34:30', '2012-10-01 21:34:30', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22156', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22158, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:41:29', '2012-07-17 21:41:29', 'Lane writes a regular column as the Mormon Media Observer for the Mormon Times. Lane teaches journalism and communication at BYU-Idaho. He is a former journalist whose scholarly interests include Mormon portrayals in the media, media and religion, and religion and politics.', 'Lane Williams', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'lane-williams', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:32:41', '2012-10-01 21:32:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22158', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22160, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:41:42', '2012-07-17 21:41:42', 'Janine wrote the screenplay for the movie based on the Jack Weyland book Charly. Janine teaches screenwriting as an adjunct faculty member at Brigham Young University Idaho.', 'Janine Gilbert', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'janine-gilbert', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:31:45', '2012-10-01 21:31:45', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22160', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22162, 2729, '2012-07-17 15:41:56', '2012-07-17 21:41:56', 'Craig is the president of Citizens for Decency, a non-profit organization trying to educate people on the detrimental effects of pornography.', 'Craig Cobia', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'craig-cobia', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:30:24', '2012-10-01 21:30:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22162', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22334, 283, '2012-07-17 15:42:11', '2012-07-17 21:42:11', 'Debra Morisie is the Senior Vice President of Human Resources at Scarborough Research, a major source for consumer shopping insights. Scarborough measures the shopping patterns, lifestyles and media habits of consumers locally, regionally, and nationally. From retail home improvement stores to cell phone and to travel, Scarborough’s measurements detail the dynamic lives of American adults.\r\n\r\nEda Ashby composed the sacred music series oratorio: "The Tree of Life: Redemptio".', 'Debbie Morisie &amp; Eda Ashby', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'debbie-morisie-eda-ashby', '', '', '2012-10-01 16:35:46', '2012-10-01 22:35:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22334', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22340, 283, '2012-07-17 15:42:28', '2012-07-17 21:42:28', 'Keith N. Hamilton has had very interesting, and a times, unique experiences as an African-American and as a convert to the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints. He has recorded some of his experiences and thoughts in his new book “Last Laborer”: Thoughts and Reflections of a Black Mormon.” Keith’s unique perspective as being one that has accomplished many “firsts” in his life including the first African American to be admitted to the BYU law School as well as one of the first Black Bishops called to serve in an LDS ward.', 'Keith Hamilton', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'keith-hamilton', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:29:11', '2012-10-01 21:29:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22340', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22349, 283, '2012-07-17 15:42:53', '2012-07-17 21:42:53', 'Rulon Nielson is the Facilities Planning/Construction Director at BYU-Idaho. In his position, Rulon has overseen the growth and construction of the physical facilities during the transition from Ricks College to BYU-Idaho, including the new 15-thousand seat BYU-Idaho Center.', 'Rulon Nielsen', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rulon-nielsen', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:28:04', '2012-10-01 21:28:04', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22349', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(22357, 283, '2012-07-17 15:43:07', '2012-07-17 21:43:07', 'Dale Churchward is a Senior Service Design Architect in the Microsoft Information Technology Group as well as the global Service Owner for Microsoft’s internal messaging applications. He received his Bachelor’s degree in Business Management from BYU. Brother Churchward’s teams in Redmond, Washington and Hyderabad, India run the services responsible for processing Microsoft’s $62.4 billion in annual revenue. He has over 15 years of experience in information technology working for such companies as: Folio Corporation, Behavioral Data Systems, AT&amp;T Wireless, Cingular Wireless, and Microsoft.', 'Dale Churchward', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dale-churchward', '', '', '2012-10-01 15:27:11', '2012-10-01 21:27:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=22357', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0);
 Educated at Harvard, Dr. Hancock holds a Ph.D. from Stanford. He leads a parallel life as a concert pianist, appearing as soloist with symphony orchestras across the nation, and holds a faculty position at Notre Dame de Namur University as artist-in-residence. A devout Mormon, he serves in presidency of the Menlo Park Stake. He and his wife Marguerite are parents of three children.\r\n', 'Russell Hancock', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'russell-hancock-2', '', '', '2013-02-19 11:37:15', '2013-02-19 18:37:15', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=33997', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(34000, 283, '2013-03-01 16:43:10', '2013-03-01 23:43:10', 'Melinda Turner is the founder of Right-Sites LLC, a web development company based in Idaho Falls, Idaho. She specializes in search engine marketing and website design. Melinda has successfully managed to blend full-time motherhood with online entrepreneurship and expertise.', 'Melinda Turner', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'melinda-turner', '', '', '2013-03-01 16:43:10', '2013-03-01 23:43:10', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=34000', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(34003, 283, '2013-03-01 16:49:29', '2013-03-01 23:49:29', 'Arthur Jue is a talent development executive, educator, writer, speaker, scholar, entrepreneur, musician, and film producer. He currently serves as director of Corporate Operations and Human Resources at Tectura, the world’s largest Microsoft enterprise solutions provider. He has extensive senior leadership experience in human resource management, learning, organization development, and technology management at companies, such as Oracle, IBM, and Hyperion. ', 'Arthur Jue', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'arthur-jue', '', '', '2013-03-01 16:49:29', '2013-03-01 23:49:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=34003', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(34061, 283, '2013-03-19 09:51:17', '2013-03-19 15:51:17', 'Frank Araugo is the CEO, owner, and founder of Araujo’s Mexican Grill/El Paisa, a quick-service Mexican restaurant chain in the San Francisco Bay Area.\r\nFrank was born in Culiacan, Sinaloa, Mexico and left his family and his homeland at the age of 14 to pursue the American dream.\r\nHe worked as a tree trimmer and a janitor before being hired as desktop support agent for Siemens AG. Over the next 16 years Frank excelled in his work and obtained additional education at both Mission College and the University of California Santa Cruz (UCSC).\r\n\r\nHe founded Silicon Valley IT Consulting and supported clients across Canada, US and Mexico. (North America).\r\nAt age 39, Frank (by then an IT Manager/Network Engineer) retired from Infineon Technologies to pursue his dream of owning his own business.\r\n\r\nA former Branch President, Frank and his lovely wife Sandra are currently serving a four-year mission for LDS Social Services.\r\n\r\nFrank and Sandra have been married for 25 years and have two daughters.', 'Frank Araujo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'frank-araujo-2', '', '', '2013-03-19 09:51:17', '2013-03-19 15:51:17', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=34061', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(34068, 283, '2013-03-19 09:55:05', '2013-03-19 15:55:05', '“Maria is President of her own company, M.L. Pribyl and Associates, and co-founder of The Tech Mentors Company. She is past President of the award winning BYU Management Society Silicon Valley Chapter and Past President of the Silicon Valley Women’s organization (affiliated with the BYU Management Society). She is a senior-level professional computer software instructor and consultant for several training companies in Silicon Valley with 20+ years of training experience. She has conducted training for clients such as Cisco Systems, NVidia, SanDisk and Stanford University. Maria also serves as 1st Counselor in the Relief Society of her ward.”', 'Maria Pribyl', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'maria-pribyl-2', '', '', '2013-03-19 09:57:23', '2013-03-19 15:57:23', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=34068', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(34071, 283, '2013-05-03 09:56:25', '2013-05-03 15:56:25', 'Marvin L. Storm is recognized as a nationally recognized entrepreneur and franchise expert with more than 25 years of experience in all aspects of entrepreneurship and franchising. His began his career after he earned his B.S. in accounting from Brigham Young University and was recruited by Deloitte Touché, a national accounting firm. He left professional/corporate life becoming a serial entrepreneur developing a specific expertise in the franchising. Marvin has started businesses from scratch, been a franchisee, a multi-unit franchisee, a regional franchise in four different franchise concepts, acquired a franchise company and has launched a franchise company from scratch.\r\n\r\nCurrently, he is the author of a recently published book, Transitioning from Employee to Entrepreneur, a book for transitional traditional world employees who are migrating into entrepreneurship. He is often a contributor to national entrepreneurial and franchise publications and publishes an entrepreneur blog at <a href="http://www.time2transition.com">www.time2transition.com</a>. He continues to focus on developing, growing and supporting franchise strategies for emerging franchise concepts.\r\n\r\nMarvin served a mission in South Africa and has served as a Bishop and in the Stake Presidency of the Oakland California Stake. He lives with in Moraga, CA and is the father of five children.', 'Marvin Storm', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'marvin-storm', '', '', '2013-05-03 09:56:25', '2013-05-03 15:56:25', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=34071', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(34074, 283, '2013-02-04 09:23:46', '2013-02-04 16:23:46', 'Alan L. Olsen is managing partner at Greenstein Rogoff Olsen & Co., LLP, a leading CPA firm in the San Francisco Bay Area. With more than 25 years of experience in public accounting, he works with some of the most successful\r\nventure capitalists in the world, developing innovative financial strategies for individuals and businesses. His firm was recently recognized by INSIDE Public Accounting as one of the Best Managed CPA firms in the USA. His firm\r\nalso garnered both local and national awards for being one of the "BestPlaces to Work", and "Fastest Growing Companies" in the Bay Area. A nationally recognized speaker, author and consultant, Alan has appeared on\r\nFox News, KPIX and KRON television networks. He has been quoted and published by various media outlets such as CNN Money, Money Magazine, Consumer Reports - Money Advisor, and Money Matters.\r\n\r\nAs chair of the Friends of Scouting Campaign, Alan raised over $1 million and in 2010 he received the Silver Beaver Award from the Boy Scouts of America for distinguished service to youth.  He continues to be active in several educational and community foundations. Alan earned a B.S. in Accounting from Brigham Young University and an MBA (Taxation)from California State University in Hayward.He was honored by more than 7,000 Bay Area alumni recognizing his continuous public service advancement and career accomplishments. Recently, he served on President Kim B. Clark''s(Former Dean of the Harvard Business School) Advancement Council at Brigham Young University-Idaho.\r\n', 'Alan Olsen', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'alan-olsen', '', '', '2013-02-04 09:23:46', '2013-02-04 16:23:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=34074', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(39758, 283, '2013-07-08 16:23:05', '2013-07-08 22:23:05', 'Mastering the 11,623-pipe Tabernacle organ is a task as enormous as the instrument itself, but through his many years of musical training and performing, Clay Christiansen and his Tabernacle organist colleagues have achieved this feat. From his seat at the organ, where he has played since 1982, Christiansen''s music breathes a unique sound that blends perfectly with the voices of the Mormon Tabernacle Choir.\r\n\r\nAs one of the Tabernacle organists, Christiansen performs and tours with the Choir, plays for the weekly Music and the Spoken Word broadcasts and the daily organ recitals. He works with the Choir''s musical staff to ensure that the organ adds the perfect musical color to the singers'' voices and the Orchestra at Temple Square. Together, this produces the Mormon Tabernacle Choir''s exquisite sound.\r\n\r\nPlaying an instrument as difficult as the Tabernacle organ requires enormous talent and experience. Christiansen completed a doctorate in composition at the University of Utah. His doctoral dissertation is a cantata for chorus, orchestra, and soprano and tenor soloists titled Isaiah, the Prophet.\r\n\r\nBefore taking his post at the Tabernacle, Christiansen served for 10 years as organist and choirmaster at Utah''s oldest non-Mormon church, St. Mark''s Episcopal Cathedral. There he became well known for his weekly radio broadcasts and popular New Year''s Eve Bach recitals. His solo performances have taken him across the United States, Canada and England. He has toured as the featured artist for groups such as the U.S. Air Force Singing Sergeants and has performed for conventions of the American Institute of Organbuilders and the American Guild of Organists.\r\n\r\nBorn in 1949, Christiansen is married to Diane Francom. They have 13 children and 43 grandchildren.', 'Clay Christiansen', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'clay-christiansen', '', '', '2013-07-08 16:23:05', '2013-07-08 22:23:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=39758', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(40476, 283, '2013-07-14 21:29:55', '2013-07-15 03:29:55', '<strong>Jonathan W. Bullen</strong> is the President of Colmena Capital with an investment focus in commercial real estate. He started his professional career in radio broadcasting and cable television operation with KVNU radio and North Utah Community TV.\r\n\r\nCurrently he serves as CEO &amp; President for the Eagle Gate College Group a five campus for profit school chain. He graduated from Utah State University in 1978 with a Bachelor of Science in Business Administration and a Minor in Economics.', 'Jonathan Bullen', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jonathan-bullen', '', '', '2013-07-14 21:29:55', '2013-07-15 03:29:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=40476', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(40479, 283, '2013-07-30 12:53:25', '2013-07-30 18:53:25', 'Producer / Writer / Director / Director of Photography\r\n\r\nAs a producer, writer, and director, T.C. Christensen is one of the brilliant minds behind the camera when it comes to these family favorites: 17 Miracles (Excel Entertainment); Emma Smith: My Story (Morning Dew); Joseph Smith: Prophet of the Restoration (LDS Church); Testaments (LDS Church); The Work &amp; the Glory (Manchester Pictures); Forever Strong (Go Films); Sea Monsters (National Geographic); Roving Mars (Disney); The Buttercreme Gang (Family Films); Rigoletto (Family Films); The Mouths of Babes (LDS Church); Finding Faith in Christ (LDS Church); Treasure in Heaven: The John Tanner Story (LDS Church); Only a Stonecutter (LDS Church).T.C. has won over 270 national and international awards for his work in directing and photography. In 2010, he was invited to join the American Society of Cinematographers.', 'T.C. Christensen Part 1', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 't-c-christensen-part-1', '', '', '2013-07-30 12:53:25', '2013-07-30 18:53:25', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=40479', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(40723, 283, '2013-07-30 12:53:49', '2013-07-30 18:53:49', 'Producer / Writer / Director / Director of Photography\r\n\r\nAs a producer, writer, and director, T.C. Christensen is one of the brilliant minds behind the camera when it comes to these family favorites: 17 Miracles (Excel Entertainment); Emma Smith: My Story (Morning Dew); Joseph Smith: Prophet of the Restoration (LDS Church); Testaments (LDS Church); The Work &amp; the Glory (Manchester Pictures); Forever Strong (Go Films); Sea Monsters (National Geographic); Roving Mars (Disney); The Buttercreme Gang (Family Films); Rigoletto (Family Films); The Mouths of Babes (LDS Church); Finding Faith in Christ (LDS Church); Treasure in Heaven: The John Tanner Story (LDS Church); Only a Stonecutter (LDS Church).T.C. has won over 270 national and international awards for his work in directing and photography. In 2010, he was invited to join the American Society of Cinematographers.', 'T.C. Christensen Part 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 't-c-christensen-part-2', '', '', '2013-07-30 12:53:49', '2013-07-30 18:53:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=40723', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(40726, 283, '2013-07-30 12:54:23', '2013-07-30 18:54:23', '<strong>Merrill N. Dibble</strong> is the Vice President of California Operations for AgReserves, Inc., a multi-national company. He oversees diverse farming and food processing operations focusing on permanent plantings such as almonds, pistachios and walnuts.\r\n\r\nHe holds a Bachelor’s degree in Agribusiness from BYU, an M.B.A. from the University of San Diego and a Master’s in Marketing from the Tecnológico de Monterrey in Mexico. He attended La Università di Padova in Italy for one year.', 'Merrill Dibble', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'merrill-dibble', '', '', '2013-07-30 12:54:23', '2013-07-30 18:54:23', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=40726', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(41230, 283, '2013-07-30 12:54:56', '2013-07-30 18:54:56', 'David Neyman is the Manager for Film &amp; Video Productions for the LDS Church Publishing Services Department at the LDS Motion Picture Studio.', 'Dave Neyman', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dave-neyman', '', '', '2013-07-30 12:54:56', '2013-07-30 18:54:56', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=41230', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(41233, 283, '2013-07-30 12:55:29', '2013-07-30 18:55:29', '<strong>Donetta Allen</strong> is Partner, Social and Digital Media Practice Leader for Hunter Public Relations. In her role as the social and digital media practice leader, she oversees agency’s clients including programming and social media for Hasbro Gaming.\r\n\r\nShe has managed accounts for Kool-Aid, Oreo, Pepperidge Farm Goldfish, Post Cereals, and Cold Stone Creamery. She holds a bachelor’s degree in Communications from BYU with an emphasis in Public Relations and a minor in French.', 'Donetta Allen', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'donetta-allen-2', '', '', '2013-07-30 12:55:29', '2013-07-30 18:55:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=41233', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(41236, 283, '2013-07-30 12:55:59', '2013-07-30 18:55:59', 'Steve has worked at BYU-Idaho, formerly Ricks College, for the past 26 years. He currently serves as the Alumni Relations director for BYU-Idaho. Managing alumni relations includes coordinating efforts of nearly 5,000 alumni volunteers and helping nearly 170,000 alumni stay connected to their alma mater. Steve’s primary focus is to establish a vibrant and active alumni network, using BYUI Connect, LinkedIn and other social media tools. <b></b>', 'Steve Davis', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'steve-davis', '', '', '2013-07-30 12:55:59', '2013-07-30 18:55:59', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=41236', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(42515, 2729, '2013-12-04 15:39:05', '2013-12-04 22:39:05', 'Born Brandon Jake Bair on Nov. 24, 1984 in Rexburg, Idaho. Has been married to wife Jordan for  5 years. They have two daughters, Brooklyn (3) and Rylee (1). Parents: Terry and Corina Bair and David and Brenda Miller. Family: Six brothers, one sister. High School (Coach): South Fremont (Cris Tucker) 2003. Red-shirted: 2006 after serving a two year church mission in Jacksonville, Florida where he became fluent in Spanish. College: Oregon, 2006-2010. Graduated June 2010 as an Economics Major, with a Minor in Spanish. NFL: 2011 Made the Kansas City Chiefs active roster. 2012 Was released from the Chiefs following the preseason at which time he was picked up by the Oakland Raiders. He was on the Raiders practice squad until the last game when he was moved to the active roster.', 'Brandon Bair', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'brandon-bair', '', '', '2013-12-04 15:54:36', '2013-12-04 22:54:36', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=42515', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(42796, 283, '2013-12-04 15:46:55', '2013-12-04 22:46:55', 'Each summer 10-12 BYU-Idaho students receive the opportunity to attend the Chicago Urban Studies tour. They spend four days in the Chicago inner city observing the living conditions and lifestyles of young men ages 12-15.\r\n\r\nThey then fly out to Victor, Idaho, where they spend the next 10 days at a camp and participate in various activities. Grover Wray, director of the program and instructor in the BYU-Idaho Department of Social Work, has been in charge of the program since 2001.\r\n\r\n"The program really lets the boys just be boys," said Wray. "It''s a wonderful and eye-opening experience for both the students and the boys."\r\n\r\nThe program started in the late 1980s when an elder''s quorum president and Relief Society president from the Hyde Park Ward in south Chicago noticed they were losing a lot of their youth to the streets. They contacted what was then Ricks College to find out if they could help in some small way. Ever since then the institution has been quietly helping and mentoring these young men.\r\n\r\n"The purpose of this program is to help these young men learn life skills," Wray said. "We want them to prepare for the challenges they''ll face in the future."\r\n\r\nThe students create their own mentoring curriculum for the camp in Victor. Wray believes that is part of the reason the program has been such a success.', 'Grover Wray', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'grover-wray', '', '', '2013-12-04 15:46:55', '2013-12-04 22:46:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=42796', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(42811, 283, '2013-12-04 15:47:59', '2013-12-04 22:47:59', 'Calee Schroeder Reed was born in Rexburg, Idaho, and grew up in San Diego, California. Her mother was a vocal coach, and Calee was taught to sing at a very young age. By the time Calee was a teenager, her sisters and her were performing in multi-part harmony all over Southern California.\r\n\r\nCalee began writing music of her own after high school – experimenting with different genres ranging from grunge rock to pop. When her mother was diagnosed with cancer, her focus turned to Christian media and worship music.\r\n\r\nAfter battling colon cancer for four years, her mother became terminally ill and Calee began writing worship music of her own as a way to sustain her faith. Calee credits Christian music for keeping her belief in God alive after her mother’s passing.\r\n\r\nShe penned The Waiting Place – her debut album – as a way to give back to the music community and reach others who find themselves experiencing similar trials in life.\r\n\r\nThe album was released by Shadow Mountain Records in May of 2012. A music video for “She Put the Music in Me” features home video and photos of Calee’s mother. All proceeds from the download of that song in May were donated to the Huntsman Cancer Foundation.\r\n\r\nCalee was married to Shaun Reed in April of 2012. They currently live in Utah.', 'Calee Reed', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'calee-reed', '', '', '2013-12-04 15:47:59', '2013-12-04 22:47:59', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=42811', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(43096, 283, '2013-12-04 15:48:48', '2013-12-04 22:48:48', 'Bob Pothier is currently the executive director of the Eastern Idaho Entrepreneurial Center as well as a partner with the RenewableTech Ventures and Epic Ventures. Prior to his work in the Eastern Idaho region, Pothier was Rockford Corporation chairman and chief executive officer. He is a graduate of the Executive Program at Stanford University and holds a bachelor’s degree in finance from Brigham Young University.\r\n\r\nBob was the Inc. Magazine Entrepreneur of the Year in the State of Arizona in 1990. In addition, he has been the owner and president of his own consulting firm, providing high-level business consultation to various multi-million dollar corporations. Bob specializes in management team building, sales and marketing strategy development. Bob and his wife are the parents of nine children and grandparents to thirty-one (and counting) grandchildren.', 'Bob and Marva Pothier', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bob-and-marva-pothier', '', '', '2013-12-04 15:49:21', '2013-12-04 22:49:21', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=43096', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 0),
(44943, 1511, '2014-02-06 10:29:33', '2014-02-06 17:29:33', '[Brightcove Video]3013045527001[/Brightcove Video]David A. Christensen is a member of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints and has served as president of the Chile Santiago North Mission and the Guatemala City Missionary Training Center. He recently took early retirement from his decades-long work on the Brigham Young University-Idaho religion faculty and is currently associated with the school as adjunct faculty while he pursues writing and humanitarian work in Honduras.<i></i>', 'David A. Christensen', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'david-a-christensen', '', '', '2014-02-06 10:49:22', '2014-02-06 17:49:22', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ldp/htdocs/?post_type=ldpshow&#038;p=44943', 0, 'ldpshow', '', 1),
